-- Dimension Data Unit Makes Offer to Purchase Integral Axon of New Zealand
-- B y   V e r n o n   W e s s e l s
-- 2010-10-06T05:00:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-06/dimension-data-s-datacraft-offers-to-acquire-integral-axon-of-new-zealand.html
Dimension Data Plc, the South African
computer-services company being bought by Nippon Telegraph &
Telephone Corp., said its Asian unit offered to buy Integral
Axon Computer Systems of New Zealand.  Didata’s Datacraft unit didn’t disclose the value of the
transaction in an e-mailed statement today.   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
